title.narrative: Delivery of regular high quality S&J advice and support across the programme cycle (including M&E) in 15 HMG Priority FCAS

description.narrative: This activity (Delivery of regular high quality S&J advice and support across the programme cycle (including M&E) in 15 HMG Priority FCAS) is a component of Provide effective security and justice advice and support (including policing) to fragile and conflict-affected states reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £1,784,530. This component benefits Africa, regional, and works in the following sector(s): Security system management and reform, Civilian peace-building, conflict prevention and resolution. , with the following implementing partners: Adam Smith International, Crown Agents Limited, Saferworld. The start date is 01-04-2012 and the end date is 30-11-2013.
